et, J., Effects of land use and eventual fire on soil erodibility in dry Mediterranean conditions (2001) For Ecol Manag, 147, pp. 15-23; Guo, L., Guifford, R., Soil carbon stocks and land use change: A meta analysis (2002) Global Change Biol, 8, pp. 345-360; Harmon, M.E., Ferrell, W.K., Franklin, J.F., Effects on carbon storage of conversion of old-growth forests to young forests (1990) Science, 247, pp. 699-701; Higgins, S., Richardson, D.M., Predicting plant migration rates in a changing world: The role of long-distance dispersal (1999) Am Nat, 153, pp. 464-475; Hódar, J.A., Castro, J., Zamora, R., Pine processionary caterpillar Thaumetopoea pityocampa as a new threat for relict Mediterranean Scots pine forests under climatic warming (2003) Biol Conserv, 110, pp. 123-129; Hulme, M., Sheard, N., (1999) Escenarios de Cambio Climático para la Península Ibérica, 6p. , Climatic Research Unit- University of East Anglia, Norwich, UK; (1990) Scientific Assessment of Climate Change - Report of Working Group I, 365p. , IPCC (Intergovernmental Panel on Cimate Change) Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; (2001) Climate Change 2001: Synthesis Report, 397p. , IPCC. WMO/UNEP, Wembley; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, 886p. , IPCC. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Iverson, L.R., Schwartz, M.W., Prasad, A.M., How fast and far might tree species migrate in the eastern United States due to climate change? (2004) Global Ecol Biogeogr, 13, pp. 209-219; Kräuchi, N., Potential impacts of a climate change on forest ecosystems (1993) Eur J For Pathol, 23, pp. 28-50; Kräuchi, N., Kienast, F., Modelling subalpine forest dynamics as influenced by a changing environment (1993) Water Air Soil Pollut, 68, pp. 185-197; Layser, E.F., Forestry and Climatic Change (1980) J For, 78, pp. 678-682; Lindner, M., Developing adaptive forest management strategies to cope with climate change (2000) Tree Physiol, 20, pp. 299-307; Lloret, F., Peñuelas, J., Estiarte, M., Experimental e